name: ipy
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "ipy" %}
{% set version = "1.01" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/IPy-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: edeca741dea2d54aca568fa23740288c3fe86c0f3ea700344571e9ef14a7cc1a

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - python >=3.6

test:
  imports:
    - IPy
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/autocracy/python-ipy
  summary: Class and tools for handling of IPv4 and IPv6 addresses and networks
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_file: COPYING
  dev_url: https://github.com/autocracy/python-ipy

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - beenje
